# Stellar App Backend Architecture

## Core Principles
1. Write concise, technical responses with accurate examples in Python.
2. Prefer iteration and modularization over code duplication.
3. Use descriptive variable names (e.g., `is_active`, `has_permission`).
4. Use lowercase with underscores for directories and files (e.g., `stellar/rate_limiter.py`).
5. Use def for pure functions and async def for I/O-bound or asynchronous operations.
6. Use type hints for all function signatures. Prefer pydantic models over raw dictionaries for input validation.
7. Explicitly handle errors and edge cases; do not rely on implicit failures.
8. Keep main.py minimal; only initialize the app, middleware, and route registration.
9. Store magic strings, environment keys, and external identifiers in constant.py.


## Root-Level Structure
```
.cursor/rules                       # Cursor project rules and AI behavior guidelines
.github/workflows                   # GitHub CI/CD workflows and deployment pipelines
.vscode                             # Editor settings and workspace configuration
stellar                             # Stellar backend source code
├── <feature_name>/                 # Feature-based API route modules (e.g. auth, users, payments)
├── api.py                          # Main API router aggregating feature routers with version prefix
├── config.py                       # Application configuration using pydantic_settings
├── constant.py                     # Global constants (e.g. ENVIRONMENT, Firebase collections)
├── main.py                         # Backend application entrypoint; initializes FastAPI app
├── rate_limiter.py                 # Rate limiting middleware configuration and exception handling
scripts                             # Project automation and utility shell scripts
tests                               # Test suites
.python-version                     # Python version specification
.dockerignore                       # Docker build exclusions
.docker-compose.yml                 # Local multi-service Docker orchestration
Dockerfile                          # Container build definition for the backend
pyproject.toml                      # Project metadata and dependency management
README.md                           # Project overview and setup documentation
uv.lock                             # Locked dependency versions for reproducible installs
```
